No! We should use only backslashes to state that "this space is not a
delimiter between arguments":

    $ export EDITOR='gvim -c "setf\ mail"'

or

    $ export EDITOR="gvim -c 'setf\\ mail'"

It would be much easier then to mess with single and double quotes.
